sequenceDiagram
    participant R as McpServerRegistry
    participant C as McpClient
    participant T as StdioTransport
    participant S as MCP server (child process)
    Note over R,S: startup (eager, skip-on-failure)
    R->>C: start()
    C->>T: initialize (protocol 2024-11-05)
    T->>S: spawn command + args · JSON-RPC over stdio
    S-->>C: capabilities · serverInfo
    C->>S: tools/list
    S-->>C: descriptors → registered as mcp__server__tool
    Note over C,S: per call (at-most-once, 20 s timeout)
    C->>S: tools/call (exactly once)
    alt success
        S-->>C: text content → tool_result
    else failure / timeout
        C->>C: poison transport · degrade to ERROR string
        Note over C: next call reconnects lazily — never re-issued
    end
